{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"31341","heading":"Persons presumed to have authority to procure necessaries","label":"31341 Persons presumed to have authority to procure necessaries","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s31341","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/stIII/ch313/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs31341","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Historical and Revision NotesRevised sectionSource section (U.S. Code)31341(a)46:972 (1st sentence), 97331341(b)46:972 (2d sentence)Section 31341(a) lists those persons who are presumed to have authority to procure necessaries for a vessel. These include the owner, master, or a manager at the port of supply; and an officer or agent appointed by the owner, charterer, owner , or buyer in possession of the vessel. This subsection makes no substantive change to law.pro hac viceSection 31341(b) provides that any person that is tortiously or unlawfully in possession of or in charge of a vessel has no authority to procure necessaries. This subsection makes no substantive change to law.","Editorial Notes","Amendments1989—Subsec. (a)(3). substituted “management” for “mangement”.Pub. L. 101–225","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective , with certain exceptions and qualifications, see , set out as a note under .Jan. 1, 1989section 107 of Pub. L. 100–710section 31301 of this title"],"amendments":["Amendments1989—Subsec. (a)(3). substituted “management” for “mangement”.Pub. L. 101–225"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s31341/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t46/s31341","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft46%2Fs31341%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"lab